        <span class="h3">F2BP Quick Tips for Getting Started</span>
        <img src="https://i.imgur.com/z5dKXPl.png" alt="">
        <p>Quick Tips for getting started without wanting to smash your laptop or mobile device:</p>
        <p>1.  Sign Up now with your name, your team name and your password.  You will have to use your password to sign in and make your future picks, so keep it memorable. As for team names, Jeff Smith has already requested, "Fightin' Flapjacks", so sorry that's taken.</p>
        <p>2.  The deadline for each round of picks is tip-off of the first game for those rounds. The F2BP Super Computer is a cold-ass bitch and any requests to make picks or change picks after the cut-off times will be treated with contempt and derision.  Make your picks by:</p>
        <p>Rounds of 64 and 32:    Thursday March 16@ 12 noon EST</p>
        <p>Rounds of 16 and 8:       Thursday March 23 @ 7 pm EST</p>
        <p>Semis and Natty Championship:   Saturday April 1 @ 12 noon EST</p>
        <p>You may edit and modify your picks as often as you want prior to the deadline.  Not that it's going to help.</p>
        <p>3.  Very important! Be sure to pick both rounds for the weekend!   Pick for the Round of 64 and the Round of 32. Then for  Sweet 16 and Elite 8.  The last week, pick for the Final Four and the Natty.   Yes, yes.  We are aware that you will be picking the Rounds of 32 and Elite 8 and the National Championship without knowing for certain which teams are playing. Deal with it.</p>
        <p>4.  Be sure to designate one game as your Daily Double.  If you forget, you're leaving meat on the bone. (see Da Rules) </p>
        <p>5.  You must wager 1/2 of your available STD's (see Da Rules) in each round.  The F2BP Super Computer will actually help you with these calculations.  </p>
        <p>6. Bookmark this site and check back here for up to the minute standings, round by round recaps, and trash talking commentary from your fellow competitors.  We will also keep an updated bracket on the site to assist you with your picks each week.</p>
        <p>7. God Have Mercy on your Soul.  And good luck.</p>
